@@ -0,0 +1,129 @@
+# bujjictl
+
+A lightweight, local-first workflow orchestration engine. Think of it as a
+single-machine, zero-dependency mini-Airflow / GitHub Actions: define
+multi-step workflows in YAML, run them with dependency-aware concurrency,
+and get a structured JSON report of exactly what happened.
+
+**Zero runtime dependencies** — pure Python standard library (≥ 3.9).
+
+## Install
+
+```bash
+pip install .
+# or for development:
+pip install -e .
+```
+
+This installs the `bujjictl` command.
+
+## Commands
+
+```text
+bujjictl validate <file.yaml>             # schema, refs, cycle checks
+bujjictl run <file.yaml> [-o report.json] # validate + execute
+bujjictl report <report.json>             # pretty-print a saved report
+```
+
+`run` exits `0` on overall success, `1` if any step failed/timed-out, `2`
+on validation error.
+
+## Workflow schema
+
+```yaml
+name: my-pipeline          # optional (defaults to filename)
+max_parallel: 4            # optional (defaults to CPU count)
+
+env:                       # optional — injected into every step
+  KEY: value
+
+defaults:                  # optional — applied where a step omits the field
+  timeout: 300             #   seconds (no timeout if omitted)
+  retries: 0               #   additional attempts after the first
+  retry_backoff: 1.0       #   base seconds; attempt N waits base * 2^(N-1)
+  shell: /bin/sh
+
+steps:
+  - id: build              # required, [A-Za-z0-9_-]+, unique
+    run: |                 # required — shell command (multi-line via |)
+      echo building
+      make all
+    needs: [other-step]    # optional — list of upstream step ids
+    env:                   # optional — merged over global env
+      CC: clang
+    timeout: 60            # optional — overrides defaults.timeout
+    retries: 2             # optional
+    retry_backoff: 2.0     # optional
+    shell: /bin/bash       # optional
+    cwd: ./subdir          # optional
+```
+
+Every step also receives `BUJJI_STEP_ID` and `BUJJI_WORKFLOW` in its
+environment.
+
+## Execution semantics
+
+- The DAG is validated up-front: unknown keys, missing/duplicate ids, bad
+  types, unknown `needs` references, self-deps and dependency cycles are
+  all reported **before** anything runs.
+- Independent steps run concurrently (bounded by `max_parallel`); a step
+  starts only once **all** of its `needs` have succeeded.
+- On non-zero exit a step is retried up to `retries` times with
+  exponential backoff (`retry_backoff * 2^(attempt-1)`).
+- A step exceeding `timeout` is sent SIGTERM (then SIGKILL) and marked
+  `timeout`.
+- When a step ultimately fails or times out, all transitive downstream
+  steps are marked `skipped` and never started. Already-running siblings
+  continue.
+- Ctrl-C cancels the run: running processes are terminated, pending steps
+  become `cancelled`.
+
+## Report format
+
+`bujjictl run` writes a JSON report (default `<name>.report.json`):
+
+```jsonc
+{
+  "workflow": "demo-pipeline",
+  "status": "success" | "failed" | "cancelled",
+  "started_at": "...", "ended_at": "...", "duration_sec": 1.23,
+  "max_parallel": 3,
+  "summary": { "success": 5, "failed": 1, ... },
+  "steps": [
+    {
+      "id": "build",
+      "status": "success" | "failed" | "timeout" | "skipped" | "cancelled",
+      "started_at": "...", "ended_at": "...", "duration_sec": 0.42,
+      "reason": "upstream 'x' failed",      // for skipped/cancelled
+      "attempts": [
+        {
+          "index": 1,
+          "started_at": "...", "ended_at": "...", "duration_sec": 0.42,
+          "exit_code": 0, "timed_out": false,
+          "stdout": "...", "stderr": "...", "error": null
+        }
+      ]
+    }
+  ]
+}
+```
+
+View it any time with `bujjictl report path/to/report.json`.
+
+## Examples
+
+```bash
+bujjictl validate examples/demo.yaml
+bujjictl run examples/demo.yaml -o demo.report.json
+bujjictl report demo.report.json
+bujjictl validate examples/broken.yaml   # shows aggregated errors
+bujjictl run examples/failing.yaml       # shows timeout + skip behaviour
+```
+
+## Notes on YAML
+
+To stay stdlib-only, `bujjictl` ships a minimal YAML loader
+(`bujjictl.miniyaml`) supporting the subset needed for workflow files:
+block mappings/sequences, inline `[a, b]` lists, `|` literal blocks,
+quoted/unquoted scalars and `#` comments. Anchors, flow mappings and
+folded `>` scalars are not supported.
